.TH "spear_mtd_read" 9 "spear_mtd_read" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
spear_mtd_read \- performs flash read operation as requested by the user
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" spear_mtd_read
.BI "(struct mtd_info *mtd "  ","
.BI "loff_t from "  ","
.BI "size_t len "  ","
.BI "size_t *retlen "  ","
.BI "u8 *buf "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mtd" 12
MTD information of the memory bank
.IP "from" 12
Address from which to start read
.IP "len" 12
Number of bytes to be read
.IP "retlen" 12
Fills the Number of bytes actually read
.IP "buf" 12
Fills this after reading
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Read an address range from the flash chip. The address range
may be any size provided it is within the physical boundaries.
Returns 0 on success, non zero otherwise
